               <floruit notBefore="1868" notAfter="1900">He was one of the 
                  two secretaries of  
                  <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> 
                  </persName>.
                  In the court of 
                  <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> 
                  </persName>, he was an indispensable assistant to the emperor. 
                  While 
                  <persName ref="PRS4359Gabrase">
                     <roleName type="title">Ṣaḥāfe tǝʾǝzāz</roleName> 
                  </persName> was in charge of the home affairs and the correspondence in Amharic,
                  Yosef thanks to his knowledge of French, was responsible for relation with foreigners and served <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/> as a kind of foreign secretary. 
                  In <date>1889</date>, he was involved in the translation of the Amharic version of  Italo-Ethiopian Treaty of Friendship and Commerce. 
                  
                    </floruit>
               
